ECr is Fully managed By aws
we no need to managed and create the server to setup the repositery,every think taken care aws
we just directly create a repositery , in those registery we can push and pull the images from the registery
**** steps ****
Launch the Ec2 Server
1-->Build server & Install the Docker,Java,Maven and AWS CLI *****  run the mvn clean package ,It is going to create the Package****  coommand for the package.
2-->Deploy server  & Install the Docker and AWS CLI

@@@@ Note to Install the AWS CLI @@@@ 
---------------------------------
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt install unzip
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install

-----------------------------
Then create the IAM Role and attach to EC2Instance 
----------------------------------------
Then Create one Repositery from ECR

BUILD THE DOCKER IMAGE IN THE BUILD SERVER
PUSH THE DOCKER IMAGE  IN THE BUILD SERVER 

THEN RUN THE RUN CONTAINER IN THE DEPLOY SERVER
